For all of you who dont know, i am now a type 2 diabetic.  But no need to worry, if i lose some weight i will be off medication, thank god, for they are <bleep>in expensive.  

Yes yes, i have changed my diet, blah blah blah.  Dont start, i hear it enough from the 'rents.

And I really encourage all of you to have your blood check to see if you are, it is really important and if you are prediabetic and change your eating habits now, no meds or anything later for you, but you do have to be careful.  I would think most insurences would cover it, it would be a preventative thing, well at least it should be.

Well i haven't updated in a long time, and this warrants an update.  

4 weeks ago we got a blue northern in Texas, which gave me a sinus infection.  As that progressed and didn't not get any better, i could not get well.  I was hoping it would only last a week and go back to school.  Well by the second week, on  Thursday, i had enough and went to the doctors center to see what was up.  They said i had a sinus infection and that was it, and gave me the shock treatment, 3 500mg antibiotics that then last 10 days.  Well, long about Saturday i had almost stopped eating and could not go to gaming, or actually to Ren faire that weekend like i had planed. On sunday i could not even keep water down in my stomach, and i called my father to come and pick me up.  He did and on monday i went to see his doctor in houston.  There they did the blood work and the other tests.  When all came back they said i had a sinus infection(duh) and another infection that looked to be mono.  Well by the end of the week i was eating, thank God, but the antibiotic he gave me, 5 750mg, plus the antihistamine, i had absolutely no energy.  Well i still had not gotten better and the next monday went back to my parents doctor, and he again ran the blood tests.  They called yesterday saying i had for sure, mono.  Well the only thing is they can not tell me at what stage of it i am at.  I am eating but i have withdrawn from school and will be getting incompletes in my classes and will have to make them up next semester, what i have not already done.  My parents and i decided to withdraw me cause i would not have the energy or the time to make up 3 weeks and do the 3 weeks of new work as well.  So i am in houston now, hopefully i will be able to come back to corpus at some point before everyone leaves for christmas, but there is no guarantee.  I was able to drive back here by myself and so i could come back, i am not contagious unless you drink after me, but we will have to see. I hope to hear from y'all through email or phone.

Birth Test Your birth date describes who we are, what we are good at and what our nborn abilities are. It also points to what we have to learn and the challenges we are facing. To figure out your Birth Number, add all the numbers in the birth date together, like in the example, until there is only one digit. A Birth Number does not prevent you from being anything you want to be, it will just color your choice differently and give you a little insight. Example March 20, 1950 3 20 1950 = 1973 1 9 7 3 = 20 2 0 = 2 2 is the Birth Number to read for the birth date in the example. #1 THE ORIGINATOR #2 THE PEACEMAKER #3 THE LIFE OF THE PARTY #4 THE CONSERVATIVE #5 THE NONCONFORMIST #6 THE ROMANTIC #7 THE INTELLECTUAL #8 THE BIG SHOT #9 THE PERFORMER # 1 - THE ORIGINATOR = 1 's are originals. Coming up with new ideas and executing them is natural. Having things their own way is another trait that gets them as being stubborn and arrogant. 1's are extremely honest and do well to learn some diplomacy skills. They like to take the initiative and are often leaders or bosses, as they like to be the best. Being self-employed is definitely helpful for them.Lesson to learn Others' ideas might be just as good or better and to stay open minded. Famous 1's Tom Hanks, Robert Redford, Hulk Hogan, Carol Burnett, Wynona Judd, Nancy Reagan, Raquel Welch. #2 - THE PEACEMAKER = 2's are the born diplomats. They are aware of others' needs and moods and often think of others before themselves. ! Naturally analytical and very intuitive they don't like to be alone. Friendship and companionship is very important and can lead them to be successful in life, but on the otherhand they'd rather be alone than in an uncomfortable relationship. Being naturally shy they should learn to boost their self-esteem and express themselves freely and seize the moment and not put things off. Famous 2's President Bill Clinton, Madonna, Whoopee Goldberg, Thomas Edison,Wolfgang Amadeus, Mozart. # 3 - THE LIFE OF THE PARTY = 3's are idealists. They are very creative, social, charming, romantic, and easygoing. They start many things, but don't always see them through. They like others to be happy and go to great lengths to achieve it.They are very popular and idealistic. They should learn to see the world from a more realistic point of view. Famous 3's Alan Alda, Ann Landers, Bill Cosby, Melanie Griffith,Salvador Dali, Jodi Foster # 4 - THE CONSERVATIVE! = 4's are sensible and traditional. They like order and routine. They only act when they fully understand what they are expected to do. They like getting their hands dirty and working hard. They are attracted to the outdoors and feel an affinity with nature. They are prepared to wait and can be stubborn and persistent. They should learn to be more flexible and to be nice to themselves. Famous 4's Neil Diamond, Margaret Thatcher, Arnold Schwarzenegger, Tina Turner, Paul Hogan, Oprah Winfrey # 5 - THE NONCONFORMIST = 5's are the explorers. Their natural curiosity, risk taking, and enthusiasm often land them in hot water. They need diversity, and don't like to be stuck in a rut. The whole world is their school and they see a learning possibility in every situation. The questions never stop.They are well advised to look before they take action and make sure they have all the facts before jumping to conclusions. Famous 5's Abraham Lincoln, Charlotte Bronte, Jessica Walter,Vincent Van Gogh, Bette Midler, Helen Keller and Mark Hamil. # 6 - THE ROMANTIC = 6's are idealistic and need to feel useful to be happy. A strong family connection is important to them. Their actions influence their decisions. They have a strong urge to take care of others and to help. They are very loyal and make great teachers. They like art or music. They make loyal friends who take the friendship seriously. 6's should learn to differentiate between what they can change and what they cannot. Famous 6's Albert Einstein, Jane Seymour, John Denver, Meryl Streep, Christopher Columbus, Goldie Hawn. #7 - THE INTELLECTUAL = 7's are the searchers. Always probing for hidden information, they find it difficult to accept things at face value. Emotions don't sway their decisions. Questioning everything in life, they don't like to be questioned themselves. They're never off to a fast start,! and their motto is slow and steady wins the race. They come across as philosophers and being very knowledgeable, and sometimes as loners. They are technically inclined and make great researchers uncovering information. They like secrets. They live in their own world and should learn what is acceptable and what not! in the world at large. Famous 7's William Shakespeare, Lucille Ball, Michael Jackson, Joan Baez, Princess Diana. # 8 - THE BIG SHOT = 8's are the problem solvers. They are professional, blunt and to the point, have good judgment and are decisive. They have grand plans and like to live the good life. They take charge of people. They view people objectively. They let you know in no uncertain terms that they are the boss. They should learn to exude their decisions on their own needs rather than on what others want. Famous 8's Edgar Cayce, Barbra Streisand, George Harrison, Jane Fonda, Pablo Picasso, Aretha Franklin, Nostrodamus #9 - THE PERFORMER = 9's are natural entertainer! s. They are very caring and generous, giving away their last dollar to help. With their charm, they have no problem making friends and nobody is a stranger to them. They have so many different personalities that people around them have a hard time understanding them. They are like chameleons, ever changing and blending in. They have tremendous luck, but also can suffer from extremes in fortune and mood. To be successful, they need to build a loving foundation. Famous 9's Albert Schweitzer, Shirley MacLaine, Harrison Ford, Jimmy Carter, Elvis Presley

well, i havent updated in like 2 weeks, ummmm  where to start.

well, i have been kinda gaming but not really, only one day a week, which is not great.  The past thursdays we have had free days.  o yeah, last thursday, i got some bling bling, if you know what i mean.  I got 2 silver necklaces and a silver dragon pendant, all sterling silver for $49 and some change,  really good deal.  and no its not stolen.  then we went to Tacoria Alcupulco(spelling), really good food, and lots of it for almost nothing.  

O yeah, i was having a crap week about 2 or 3 weeks ago, when i last posted, but now i am doing better.  But everyone else is haveing a bad week.  My other self, carol, and a kinda friend katherine(way to much explination about her).  Drama is everywhere, and its not mine so its doing good.  Saterday I helped a friend move out of her house, and she is a happy panda.  

O friday, (man i cant put this in chronological order, i am putting stuff here as it flow from my mind. is this good or bad, maybe i need to organize my thoug..h.t..s,  right the post) I went, skipping anime club(i didnt feel up to it), and went to play pool with mikey, and friends.  afterwords we went to chilies, and then a strip club.  the club was alright, but not anything to write home about, if you would really want to write home about going to a strip club, i guess your father might want to know.  anyways, we went back to my place and watched underworld and played TMNT pizza power game.  i won.  Carol had a bad headache and had some drink, so she got to sleep on the air matress.

o yeah, the weekend of the 20 i went home, (really need to organize thoughts) i went home.  got money from parents and grandparents, and saw josh, and jason and darrell.  Played pool with the latter 3, on saterday for free, cause of joshs friend who is like a older sister, and we got then go to chilies. o the night before we went to pohi, or ihop if u really want to know, and saw memorialites, i hate them, and the dude who was sitting at the register hated them as much as i, it was great. 

anyways thats the best parts of my weeks that i havent posted.

well i am in a gaming group on Thursdays, Saterdays, and Mondays.  Tonight we played a game of Dungeons and Dragons, in the DragonLance campaign setting.  Its great.  However, we did not have two of out players.  A cleric, which we needed, and a barbarian.  They were captured.  However, the clarics mom is going into surgery and will be out for a few weeks.  But all in all a good game.  I am playing a human fighter, who is both a close and ranged specialty.  Theres our ranger, our other barbarian and a kender handler.  I killed so many people, its great.


Just as a side note: those following my personal life, she wont be going on another date with me.  At least as my girlfriend.  She does not fell the same way I do for her.  But we are not going to stop being friends, and thats good.  Josh, do not treaten me or anything, i am not going to disappear or run away, i will continue to be her friend and to be around her.  Which is very important, one way or another I want to be around her, but I REFUSE to make her do something that she does not want to do.  If she is not comfertable or does not want to date me then I wont make her.  But i did tell her that I do love her, and that she is beautiful, smart and sexy, no matter what anyone says. 
We both made several promises:
1. to tell each other the truth
2. we are not going to disappear from each others lives

Which makes me very happy.  

And no I did not use her name, cause its not fair to her if I do.
